<span style="color: #3d2603;"><strong> Costa Rica is considered to possess the highest density of biodiversity of any country worldwide. While encompassing just one third of a percent of Earthâ€™s landmass, approximately the size of West Virginia, in United States. Hundreds of species are endemic to Costa Rica, meaning they exist nowhere else on earth. These endemic species include frogs, snakes, lizards, finches, hummingbirds, gophers, mice, cichlids, and gobies among many more.</strong></span></h6>";s:10:"post_title";s:22:"Wildlife of Costa Rica";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:22:"wildlife-of-costa-rica";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2016-02-02 18:51:40";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2016-02-02 18:51:40";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:33:"http://www.experience.cr/?p=24628";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}}